conditional operator:The Conditional Operator (also called the ternary operator)
is a short way to write an if–else statement in one line.
-how it works
  condition is checked first.
  If the condition is true, expression1 is executed.
  If the condition is false, expression2 is executed.

ex:
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int a = 10, b = 20, max;

    max = (a > b) ? a : b;

    printf("Maximum = %d", max);
    return 0;
}
